==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unbridled
<hw>Un*bri"dled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>bridled</ets>.]</ety> <def>Loosed from the
bridle, or as from the bridle; hence, unrestrained; licentious; violent;
<as>as, <ex>unbridled</ex> passions</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Unbridled</xex> boldness.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lands deluged by <qex>unbridled</qex> floods.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*bri"dled*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>
<rj><au>Abp. Leighton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbroken</ent>⟦br⟧
